# Builder.io rules

## Stack
- Framework: Next.js (App Router)
- Language: TypeScript — strict mode, no `any`
- Styling: Tailwind CSS — use utility classes only, no inline styles
- Components: React functional components with named exports

## Components
- Always check `app/components/ui/` before generating new primitives
- If Button, Card, Input, or Badge exist there — import and use them
- Do not create duplicate components

## Code style
- Named exports only — no default exports except page-level files
- Every component needs an explicit TypeScript props interface
- Keep components small — split anything over ~100 lines

## Commands (run on changed files only)
- Type check: `npx tsc --noEmit src/path/to/file.tsx`
- Lint: `npx eslint --fix src/path/to/file.tsx`
- Format: `npx prettier --write src/path/to/file.tsx`

## Do not
- Hardcode colours — use Tailwind tokens
- Install new packages without noting it in the PR description
- Generate new utility functions if one exists in `src/lib/`